# remove all non-whitespace, non-comma and new line characters, remove multiple spacing, and
# lower case the string and split into tokens

train['token_comments'] = train['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: re.sub(r'[^\w\s,]+', '', x))\
.apply(lambda x: re.sub(r'[\n]*','',x)).apply(lambda x: re.sub(r' +', ' ',x)).apply(lambda x: x.lower().split(' '))

test['token_comments'] = test['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: re.sub(r'[^\w\s,]+', '', x))\
.apply(lambda x: re.sub(r'[\n]*','',x)).apply(lambda x: re.sub(r' +', ' ',x)).apply(lambda x: x.lower().split(' '))

# Tokenize all the columns and remove english stopwords and empty strings.
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))

tokens=[]
for row in train['token_comments']:
    for token in row:
        if token not in stop_words and (token != ''):
            tokens.append(token)
In [15]:
# Frequency distribution of tokens and sorted descensind order to find most common occuring words. 
freq = nltk.FreqDist(tokens)
items = sorted(freq.items(), key= lambda kv: kv[1], reverse=True)

        for token in row:
            if token not in stop_words and (token != ''):

from wordcloud import WordCloud

def wordcloud(freqd,label):
    wc = WordCloud(width=1200, height=800,
                  background_color='black',
                  max_words=200)
    wc.generate_from_frequencies(freqd)
    
    fig=plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.imshow(wc,interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.tight_layout(pad=0)
    plt.title('label: {}'.format(label), size=15)
    plt.show()

count of punctuations

count of stop words

df['count_sent'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len(nltk.sent_tokenize(str(x))))

df['count_words'] =df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len((str(x)).split()))
# using nltk.word_tokenize(str(x)) works as well but it includes non-word tokens including punctuationse etc. 

df['count_unique_words'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len(set(str(x).split())))

df['count_punctuations'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len([w for w in str(x) if w in string.punctuation]))

df['count_captital'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len([w for w in str(x) if w.isupper()]))

df['count_stop_words'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len([w for w in str(x).lower().split() if w in stop_words]))

df['mean_word_len']= df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: np.mean([len(w) for w in str(x).split()]))

df['count_nonAlpha'] = df['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: len(re.findall(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9_ ]', str(x))))

def top_n_tfidf(tfidf, topn=25):
    
    top_feats = []
    
    for label in labels:
        ids = train[labels].index[train[label]==1]
        td = train_unigrams[ids].toarray()
        td_means = np.mean(td, axis=0)
        top_tf = np.argsort(td_means)[::-1][:20]
        top_feats.append([(label, feature_names[i], td_means[i]) for i in top_tf])
    
    items = [x for y in top_feats for x in y]
    #tfdf = pd.DataFrame(items)
    #tfdf.columns = ['label', 'feature', 'tfidf']
    return items
